E
charter stone~
The four faces of the tall charter stone record rights of passage for all twelve recognized approach routes. Each face covers three routes with legal text, distance markers, and water-draw entitlements. The south face, facing the barricade, has been deliberately defaced: a deep gouge runs through the entitlement text, obliterating the clause that guaranteed free passage to any caravan presenting a valid water-court charter.
~
