#1951
@@yPalm Ring Threshold@@N~
@@yThe character of the world changes at this exact point:@@N the last meter of open desert gives way to the first fronds of the palm ring's outer edge, and the air shifts from searing heat to a shaded coolness that is almost physical in its contrast. @@aThe palm crowns overhead filter the light to a green-gold shimmer,@@N and the smell of hot sand is replaced by the smell of water, green growth, and the faint mineral tang of the oasis springs. @@bThe ground underfoot changes from packed sand to a mixture of sand and dark loam,@@N still firm but with the give of soil that receives regular water. The transition is sudden enough that travelers instinctively pause at this line — the body registers the change before the mind does. Behind lies the barricade-haunted approach, the toll-burned wagons, and the reaver captain's flag. Ahead lies the Great Oasis itself: the basin, the palm ring, the springs, and everything that survives of the civilization that was built here.
~
