@@yCaravan Receiving Yard Remains@@N~
@@yThe old caravan receiving yard at the oasis's eastern margin has been stripped of its movable infrastructure,@@N leaving only the stone inspection platforms, the permanent weighing-station base, and the iron hobble-rings set into the ground at regular intervals for animal tying. @@bThe yard's southern edge was enclosed by a low wall that still stands,@@N its interior now used by Sand Jackals as a sheltered nesting ground — the animals have learned that the Spring Wardens will not drive them out of the oasis. A Midgaard Scholar's tent is pitched in the wall's shelter, the scholar having obtained Warden permission to study the old weighing-station's inscribed calibration standards. The receiving yard's northern connection to the oasis road network ended when the reavers took over the approach corridor, making this space a historical artifact rather than a functioning infrastructure point.
~
