#1960
@@aThe Last Garden@@N~
@@aThe south shore of the basin hosts the only surviving cultivated garden in the eastern desert:@@N a terraced plot of date palms, medicinal herbs, flowering plants, and culinary roots maintained by the Last Reed Tender in the tradition of the Reed Tender caste that once numbered dozens. @@aThe garden is a small miracle of hydraulic management:@@N basin-edge seepage waters the lowest terrace through a system of clay channels the Tender maintains daily, while the upper terraces receive measured allocations from the warden sluice schedule. @@bThe smell of the garden — green and complex against the mineral-sharp oasis air — is unlike anything else in the eastern desert.@@N The Tender knows every plant individually, knows its history and cultivation notes going back three generations, keeps the knowledge in written records stored in a waterproofed jar. The garden is the only place in the oasis where the Ledger Kingdom's ornamental planting tradition survives in practice.
~
