E
waystone western face~
The western face records the heading to the Eastern Desert road's first waypoint, the travel time from the oasis under standard load conditions, and the water-draw entitlement for caravans arriving by the western route. The legal formula at the bottom reads in archaic charter-script: any traveler who reaches this stone by the western road has the right to draw water in the amount of their charter's measure. The formula is unchanged from the original Keeper drafting.
~
