southwestern waystone compact text~
The Twin Basin Compact inscription reads in formal water-court script: each basin owes to the other the water of three days and the passage of messengers without toll. The formula was drafted in the thirty-second year of the High Water Court and ratified by both oasis communities in a ceremony at which the identical inscription was cut into the Southwestern Waystone of the Southern Oasis. The southern oasis's copy may still exist.
~
