@@bA natural alcove in the palm ring's dense inner growth has been reinforced with timber framing to create a dry storage space for the Spring Wardens' militia equipment.@@N @@bWeapons racks hold a modest arsenal — spears, short blades, a few bows and their quivers@@N — maintained against the possibility that the current uneasy balance of power at the oasis breaks down. The equipment is well-maintained despite its modest quantity, each piece cleaned, sharpened, or strung on a regular schedule that the Watch Captain personally enforces. A duty roster on the alcove's back wall shows the militia's rotation schedule. The alcove is not secret — the reavers know it exists, and the Synod knows it exists — but neither has moved against it because both understand that provoking the Wardens to arm their community would cost more than either side wants to pay.
