@@aWarden Watch Tower@@N~
@@aThe Spring Wardens' observation tower is the tallest structure in the living oasis — three tiers of fitted stone and salvaged timber that gives a clear sightline over the palm ring to all three primary approach directions.@@N @@aA Warden Watch Captain maintains post at the tower during daylight hours,@@N equipped with a signal horn and a written code of responses for each of the threat types the Wardens have categorized. @@yFrom the tower's upper tier, the Toll Pavilion ruins are visible above the palm ring's southern edge,@@N showing the extent of Synod occupation: hanging censers, painted jackal sigils, and the movement of robed figures through the broken colonnade. The tower was built in the Water Court period as a fire-watch station, converted to its current role by the Wardens when the Basin fell. A small bronze bell mounted at the tower's peak can be heard anywhere in the oasis community.
