@@pSalt Oath Chamber@@N~
@@pThe Salt Oath Chamber is where the Wellmouth Creed formalizes its membership — an initiation space in which new acolytes take the oaths that bind them to the Creed's doctrine and discipline under the Hierophant's spiritual authority.@@N @@pConcentrated salt circles have been drawn on the chamber floor with costly imported salt,@@N each circle's diameter corresponding to a different oath grade — the innermost circle reserved for initiates taking their final binding oath. @@pRitual basins at the chamber's four corners hold water drawn from different depths in the cistern ring@@N — the Creed's theology assigns different spiritual properties to water from different levels of the aquifer. The chamber walls carry the Oath Text in full, lettered in copper oxide paint that has turned a deep blue-green over years of incense exposure. The smell of the chamber is dominated by mineral salt overlaid with the Creed's incense — an uncomfortable combination that the theology frames as spiritually clarifying.
