#1987
@@pAntechamber of the Mouth@@N~
@@pThe antechamber immediately outside the Hierophant's sanctum has been dedicated to the Creed's most intensive devotional practice:@@N twenty-four hour prayer vigils maintained by rotating teams of Wellmouth Priests who kneel in the chamber and direct their prayers into the floor, which the Creed believes transmits sound to the sleeping earth deity below. @@pThe floor has been polished smooth by years of kneeling worship,@@N and the stone in the chamber's center carries a shallow depression from the repeated pressure of foreheads touching in the prayer posture. @@pA narrow slot cut in the floor beside the depression is the Creed's listening point — an ear pressed to the slot can hear,@@N on still days, the faint sound of water moving deep in the cistern ring below. The Creed interprets this sound as the earth deity's answer to prayer. The slot was originally a drainage opening for the cistern engineers' maintenance work.
~
