#1988
@@pBlood Libation Pool@@N~
@@pThe libation pool was originally a Water Court drainage feature — a shallow basin in the pavilion floor connected to the cistern ring by a channel designed to carry overflow away from the judicial spaces during flood season.@@N The Wellmouth Creed has repurposed it as their primary ritual offering space: the drainage channel now carries offering material down into the cistern channels below, the Creed's theology interpreting this as direct communication with the spring deity through the earth's own hydraulic system. @@pOffering stain patterns radiate from the pool in concentric marks that have built up over years of ritual use,@@N recording the shape of hundreds of ceremonies in layers of dried mineral and organic material. @@RThe pool's contents are not water.@@N The metallic smell in this room is from the offering material itself. Wellmouth Priests who maintain the pool wear protective linen wraps on their arms and faces.
