@@lThe upper level of the sluice gallery was designed to give the North Cistern's sluice master a comprehensive view of the flow regulation system:@@N viewing ports in the gallery's floor look down into the actual cistern chambers below, and a series of control rods along the east wall connect to the sluice gates that regulate water distribution between the four cistern chambers. @@lMost of the control rods are corroded past function, but two still move freely,@@N their mechanism maintained by the Spring Wardens for the North Cistern's continuing operation. Calibration marks on the gallery walls show the expected rod positions for different flow conditions — winter surplus, summer base, drought minimum — and the current rod positions confirm the Wardens are running the system at drought-minimum settings even in what should be a moderate water year. @@bThe viewing ports show dark water moving far below.@@N
