#1994
@@lCalibration Obelisk Chamber@@N~
@@lA stone obelisk rises in the center of this chamber — not a decorative monument but a functional instrument: a calibrated measurement column whose faces record the target water levels for the cistern ring under twelve different operational scenarios.@@N @@lEach face carries a different scenario in the Keepers' engineering notation:@@N flood surplus, seasonal base, drought emergency, distribution lockdown, and eight intermediate states. The current operational state can be read by comparing the actual water visible through the viewing port in the floor to the level marks on the obelisk's nearest face. @@bThe obelisk's inscriptions are in the Keepers' most technical register@@N — the engineering dialect that only the sluice masters and their training documents translated for operational use. The Spring Wardens have a partial translation copy in the wellhead ledger, sufficient to operate the system at its simplest settings.
