#2000
@@yThe Ledger Vault@@N~
@@yThe Ledger Vault is the Keepers' greatest surviving archive — a room built specifically to protect the master copies of the water-debt ledgers, charter documents, and astronomical tables that formed the administrative foundation of the entire eastern road network.@@N @@yThe vault's construction reflects the value of its contents:@@N walls twice the thickness of the surrounding cistern chambers, a stone door whose pivots still work despite centuries of use, and a ventilation system that maintains a constant humidity level to preserve the salt tablets and clay documents within. @@lMost of the archive is intact.@@N The Battle of the Dry Basin destroyed the Toll Pavilion above and collapsed two cistern chambers, but the vault's builders anticipated structural stress and the room has held. Salt tablets in carved stone racks, rolled clay documents in sealed ceramic tubes, and the water-debt ledger volumes in bound form fill every available surface. @@yThe archive contains the legal and administrative history of oasis civilization@@N — and almost no one knows it survived.
~
