0 -1 2001
E
salt tablets~
Hundreds of salt tablets fill the vault's primary racks, each tablet recording a water-right transaction, charter registration, or administrative decision of the High Water Court. The tablets are organized by year and case number in a filing system that the vault's own indexing documents explain. The most recent tablets are dated approximately three generations ago — the last period of active Water Court administration before the Battle of the Dry Basin.
~
E
ledger volumes~
The water-debt ledger volumes record every water draw from the oasis basin and cistern ring for over a century of Water Court administration. Each volume covers one year and contains entries for every caravan and resident draw. The final volume ends mid-year with a note in a different hand: court suspended pending resolution of dry basin dispute. The resolution never came.
~
