@@lThe anteroom outside the Ledger Vault served as the vault's security checkpoint — the space where visiting administrators were verified, their documents checked, and their access level confirmed before the vault door was opened.@@N @@lA stone verification desk is still in place on the east wall,@@N its surface scarred by the iron stylus that clerks used to record visitor information in the access log. The access log itself is stored inside the vault. @@bThe anteroom floor carries the wear patterns of intensive administrative use@@N — a groove worn into the stone where chairs were habitually pulled out from the desk, and a smooth patch where a queue of waiting visitors stood. A western branch passage leads toward the dry West Cistern, while the main route continues south deeper into the cistern ring.
~
