E
final inscription~
Below the last flow record, someone carved: the cistern engineers of the west quarter, who maintained this chamber from its first season to its last, record here that we did our work correctly. The drought did not come from any failure of this chamber. The Ninth Meridian Rite was not our decision. This chamber was built well and may be restored when the water returns. The inscription is in the Keeper's most formal engineering script.
~
