@@lDrowned Gallery Entry@@N~
@@lThe gallery immediately below the flooded stairwell is fully submerged — the ceiling is visible through the cold, clear water, and the mineral-coated walls carry Keeper inscriptions that are legible through the water's clarity despite being six feet below the current surface.@@N @@lThe submersion has paradoxically preserved some inscription details that surface water and weather would have eroded:@@N the lettering here is the sharpest in the entire cistern ring, each character crisp and deep, the engineering notation as readable as if it were cut last season. Something large left a passage through the mineral growth on the gallery's south wall — a scrape mark at a height that implies the passage-maker was significantly larger than a person. The gallery's ceiling lights the water with a faint phosphorescence from mineral-reactive organisms that colonized the vaulted stone after the flooding.
~
