#2015
@@lLower Stairwell Flood@@N~
@@lThe lower section of the original stairway system — the secondary stairs that gave maintenance workers access to the deepest cistern levels — is here entirely submerged, its stone steps leading down into darkness that the eye cannot penetrate even in clear water.@@N @@lThe clarity of the flooded gallery diminishes at this point:@@N the water carries a fine suspended mineral particulate from the aquifer pressure that stirs sediment in the deeper passages. The particulate gives the water a faint blue-grey opacity that limits visibility to several arm-lengths. Something has disturbed the sediment recently — a cloud of particulate larger than any small creature could generate hangs in the lower water column, slowly dispersing in the southward current. The walls carry blast-damaged sections where the Battle of the Dry Basin's underground fighting reached this depth, the stone spalled and fractured in irregular patterns.
~
