#2016
@@lSubmerged Archive@@N~
@@lThe overflow collection gallery that became the archive chamber holds the most heartbreaking discovery in the flooded East Cistern:@@N an entire secondary archive of Keeper documents, sealed in ceramic tubes and placed in stone wall-niches, now completely submerged but partially legible through the cold, clear water. @@lThe ceramic tubes have sealed their contents against the flooding@@N — the documents inside are likely still readable if recovered — but the archive has been disturbed. Several niches are empty, their tubes removed. The disturbance pattern does not match human entry: the empty niches are at inconsistent heights and the surrounding mineral growth has been scraped away by something that moved without the careful attention a human archivist would apply. @@lSomething brought objects here from outside and deposited them alongside the undisturbed tubes.@@N The deposited objects — bone fragments, a bronze seal disk, several smooth river stones — are not archive material.
~
