0 -1 2014
E
archive tubes~
The surviving ceramic tubes are sealed with wax and bronze clamps that have resisted the water. Their label inscriptions, visible through the clear water, identify the contents as secondary copies of astronomical observation records — the Keepers' sky-watching data from three generations of observations. Several tubes are cracked at their seals and their contents are certainly destroyed. The undamaged tubes could be retrieved and their contents read, if someone was willing to dive for them.
~
