#2017
@@lAquifer Passage North@@N~
@@lThe passage deepens here as it approaches the zone where the East Cistern's artificial construction gives way to natural aquifer channels cut by the underground water over centuries.@@N @@lThe transition is visible in the walls: fitted limestone blocks above, natural limestone formation below,@@N the Keepers' construction ending at a precise line where their engineering met the existing geology and stopped. Below the line, the walls carry the striations of natural water-flow — horizontal grooves cut by current over ages, recording the aquifer's behavior before any human intervention shaped it. The mineral phosphorescence on the ceiling is stronger here, the organisms more dense in the natural stone than in the Keeper-cut sections. @@lThe current is stronger now,@@N pulling southward with enough force to require active swimming to maintain position.
~
