#2018
@@lBranching Aquifer Gallery@@N~
@@lThe natural aquifer channel branches here into two descending passages with a side gallery to the east,@@N the geological split having been present long before the Keepers built their cistern above it. @@lThe Keepers documented this branching in their original survey:@@N a carved marker on the upstream face of the branch point records the directional designations they assigned — east gallery for overflow documentation, south passage for primary aquifer access — in the same notation they used for their engineered spaces. The natural walls carry a record of the aquifer's history in their mineral layers: dark bands of iron oxide, pale calcium carbonate, and the blue-green of copper-bearing water marking different periods of the underground geology's evolution. @@lSomething very large uses both branches regularly,@@N the scrape marks on both sides of the split too wide to be a single creature moving carefully.
~
