#2019
@@lMineral-Veined Corridor@@N~
@@lThe aquifer corridor's natural walls are at their most spectacular here, the mineral veining complex enough to constitute a geological record of the aquifer's entire accessible history:@@N white calcite veins over copper-blue malachite over iron-red ochre, the layers as legible as pages in a mineral book. @@lA biologist from Midgaard who reached this point — recorded in a journal fragment found in the submerged archive above — spent three days mapping the veining and identified seven distinct mineral periods representing at least twelve hundred years of aquifer behavior.@@N The journal fragment ends mid-sentence, the biologist apparently having left or been interrupted. The corridor carries a strong current now, the passage narrowing enough that the aquifer's full pressure focuses through it, making progress south a matter of sustained effort against the flow. @@lA low vibration in the walls is the aquifer itself, the living pressure of the underground water system that keeps the oasis alive.@@N
~
