#2020
@@lAquifer Channel@@N~
@@lThe eastern side gallery of the branching aquifer is where the natural water channel is at its most active:@@N here a secondary spring joins the main aquifer flow from a crack in the east wall, its water distinctly warmer than the surrounding temperature and carrying a mineral content that the wall precipitation records as a different chemistry from the main aquifer. @@lThe spring vent has been partially excavated — the crack widened to twice its natural size by something that worked the limestone with deliberate, sustained effort.@@N The excavation pattern does not match any human tool-work; the marks are irregular impressions rather than cut surfaces, as if made by something that applied direct physical pressure rather than a cutting instrument. @@lThe current pulls southward down the main passage,@@N but a countercurrent from the eastern spring pushes back against the gallery's east wall, creating a circulation pattern that the Keepers' mineral precipitation marks confirm has been stable for at least three generations.
~
