@@lWyrm's Antechamber@@N~
@@lThe antechamber before the Wyrm's lair is the first partially-drained space in the flooded zone:@@N a high natural vault above the aquifer channel allows an air pocket to persist here, the ceiling above the waterline dry and covered in mineral stalactites whose growth records the centuries during which this space has held air. @@lShed wyrm scales cover the antechamber's raised stone shelf along the east wall@@N — the creature apparently uses this shelf to rest with its upper body in air, its lower body remaining in the water. The scales are extraordinary objects: each one a hand-length across, hard as stone, and colored with the blue-grey iridescence of deep aquifer minerals that have been incorporated into the creature's physical structure over its long habitation. @@lThe spring vent side chamber opens east from here.@@N To the south, the passage narrows again before opening into the Wyrm's actual lair. The temperature in the air pocket is still cold, but breathable. The sound of the wyrm's movement in the deep water below is periodic and immense.
~
