@@lSpring Vent Chamber@@N~
@@lThe spring vent chamber east of the Wyrm's antechamber is where one of the three original Deepwell Confluence springs rises — a natural spring vent in the limestone floor that predates all human presence at the oasis, the original source of the water that made the Great Oasis possible.@@N @@lThe spring vent is active.@@N @@aWater rises through the vent continuously, cold and mineral-clear, bubbling up into the chamber and overflowing into the main aquifer channel through a natural sill.@@N @@lThe vent's activity is maintained by the Wyrm's presence: the creature regularly clears the vent of mineral sediment that would otherwise seal it over time,@@N using its body to displace the deposits that accumulate at the spring's emergence point. The clearing is not deliberate stewardship — the Wyrm uses the vent as a temperature reference point and clears it incidentally as it moves through the chamber. The spring does not know or care about the creature's motivation. It simply flows, as it has always flowed, keeping the oasis alive from below.
