E
spring vent~
The limestone spring vent is approximately a forearm's diameter at its surface emergence, widening as it descends into the fractured rock below. The water emerging from it is measurably colder than the surrounding aquifer water and carries a different mineral signature — geologists who have studied similar vents elsewhere describe this as evidence of a different aquifer layer, deeper and older than the primary cistern supply. This spring has been flowing since before the Keepers surveyed the oasis. It has never gone dry in recorded history.
~
S
