#2031
@@lLair of the Oasis Wyrm@@N~
@@lThe Wyrm's primary lair is a natural cathedral space in the deep aquifer limestone — a chamber whose scale the Keepers documented with evident astonishment in their survey records, noting that it represented a void of such size that its stability was paradoxical and should be studied further.@@N The study did not continue long enough. @@lThe chamber's floor is the second spring vent of the original Deepwell Confluence:@@N a broad, flat limestone plate perforated by dozens of small vents and three primary vent openings large enough to admit a person, through which the aquifer flows upward with constant, steady pressure that has never faltered. @@lThe Wyrm is here.@@N Coiled around the largest spring vent in a mass of mineral-encrusted scales and cold muscle, the creature occupies the chamber as completely as if it was grown here, which in some sense it was — the Wyrm has been in residence long enough that its body has incorporated the chamber's mineral environment and the chamber's environment has been shaped by the creature's presence. @@lKilling it would drain the springs.@@N @@RSomething that large does not die quietly, and the spring vents it clears are not small.@@N
~
