0 -1 2539
E
wyrm scales~
Up close, the Wyrm's scales are the most complex natural material in the oasis — each one a layered composite of the creature's own biological material and the aquifer's dissolved minerals, built up over decades of deep-water habitation. The scale color shifts between angles: blue-grey in direct light, copper-green in phosphorescent light, nearly black in shadow. The largest scales at the creature's mid-body are the size of a buckler shield and harder than cut limestone.
~
E
spring vents~
The three primary spring vents in the lair floor are the original sources of the Deepwell Confluence — the springs whose existence made the Great Oasis possible before human civilization arrived to use them. The vents flow at a rate that has remained consistent for as long as records have been kept, and their output feeds everything above: the basin, the cistern ring, the garden terraces, the wells in the warden settlement. The Wyrm's body partially seals two of the three vents, but the pressure is sufficient that the water forces its way through regardless.
~
S
